The paper focuses on the evaluation of automated analysis tools for Ethereum smart contracts, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the Solidity programming language (cs.PL) and the execution framework used for the evaluation (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper touches on system and control theory (cs.SY) in the context of analyzing the behavior of smart contracts.
